-- U.S. Tourist Stabbed to Death in Jerusalem Hills While Hiking With Friend
-- B y   C a l e v   B e n - D a v i d
-- 2010-12-19T08:38:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/two-woman-attacked-one-slain-in-jerusalem-hills-police-say.html
Two women were attacked and one was
killed while hiking in the hills south of Jerusalem over the
weekend, Israel police said. The slain woman was a U.S. citizen
visiting Israel, according to local media reports.  The injured woman was found yesterday with multiple stab
wounds, said  Micky Rosenfeld , a police spokesman, and is in
moderate-to-serious condition at Jerusalemâ€™s Hadassah Hebrew
University Medical Center at Ein Kerem. The body of the
murdered woman was discovered this morning, police said.  The injured woman, Kay Susan Wilson, who holds British
citizenship and lives in Israel, told police she and her friend
were attacked by two Arab men while hiking in a wooded hilly
area south of Jerusalem that borders the West Bank. The other
woman has been identified as Christine Logan, a U.S. tourist,
The Jerusalem Post  reported  without saying how it obtained the
information.  Police are investigating whether the incident was a
terrorist or criminal attack, Rosenfeld said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
